Actress Yvonne Jegede believes Afrobeat musician, Seun Kuti is worthy of being celebrated. The mother of one expressed her sincere wishes for the son of Afrobeat legend, Fela Anikulapo Kuti, as he turned 39. Jegede says Kuti is not just a friend to her but a personality, who is worth celebrating always.   Davido hits the gym after deal with Puma     Skit maker De General arrested as NDLEA raids home     Learn ‘toasting’ women as you can no longer get them with…   “Happy birthday to this genius of a friend, Seun Kuti. I celebrate you not just because it’s your birthday but you are worthy of celebrating. I love you, my dear friend,” she wrote. - Advertisement - Friends of Seun Kuti have been felicitating with him as he celebrated his 39th birthday on Tuesday, January 11, 2021.